Statistical Summary
The average house price is around ₹3–4 lakh.
Most houses have 3 bedrooms.
House sizes vary from smaller apartments to larger family homes.
Standard deviation shows moderate variation in prices.


Correlation
Price and SqFt show a strong positive correlation.
This means larger houses generally cost more.
Price and Age usually show a negative correlation, meaning older houses tend to be cheaper.



Distribution
The histogram shows that house prices are slightly right-skewed.
A few expensive houses create a long tail on the right.
The box plot reveals possible outliers.
The KDE plot confirms that most houses are concentrated in the middle price range.


